name: New Gibbons Residence Hall Building B5
directions: Through the front door facing the B courtyard, go through the lobby and take a left at the hallway. Go up the stairs at the end to the second floor. Take a left and then a right, it's the first door on the right, with the card reader.
comment:
You have to be a resident to use the bathroom, or let in by a resident. If you're visiting, this restroom is an easy option for you so long as your host is willing to swipe for you.
This hall is part of the Rainbow Perspectives residence community on the Rutgers Cook campus. The whole floor is gender-neutral so it's a great option to live.

name: Rutgers Center for Social Justice Education and LGBT Communities
directions: Upstairs (right in front of the main entrance) and to the left down a hallway. If you get lost just ask! May not be open late evening or on weekends.
comment: Single-person bathroom, like one found in most houses. The SJE is a very, very safe place for people of all sexes, genders, and orientations, as well as all other minorities. It's located in a small two-story house on the Rutgers College Avenue campus. They also have free resources available.

name: Nurse's Office at Sierra Vista High School
directions: Nurse's office in the center quad. It is to your right when you face the stage. The door next to the cafeteria door. Knock or walk in. Once you are allowed in the restroom will be to your left.
comment:
You have to be a student. The nurse has to be there to open the door. Just say you came for the neutral restroom. She has instructions to let anyone use it.

If she is not there you could ask the teacher in the third floor (tall building) in Room 608 if she could open the teacher restroom for you. It is across from her door. Please only ask when she is not lecturing the class (brunch,lunch, after school). Say Rosie&Becca from 2016 sent you. Her name is Mrs. Graf by the way. Teacher's restroom is only temporary / for emergencies (students are actually not supposed to be let in but she's friendly).
